{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_01VR8BARV6C52tnxpZAtKdSQ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_013ji8Ec5fBcgcGH2ysB2hDB","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/routes/profile.ts"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":5,"cache_creation_input_tokens":5033,"cache_read_input_tokens":41796,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":5033,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01VCdhEkVHxr9GNyPLZrZRLq","session_id":"91d95e74-c305-4801-b7f4-b036b613409b","uuid":"888c927f-ce0f-452c-a23c-f46ca0a0a147"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_013ji8Ec5fBcgcGH2ysB2hDB","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * Profile routes — transaction history for the authenticated player.\n     3→ */\n     4→\n     5→import { Hono } from \"hono\";\n     6→import type { AppEnv } from \"../hono-env.js\";\n     7→import type { Db } from \"../db.js\";\n     8→import { logger } from \"../logger.js\";\n     9→\n    10→export interface ProfileRoutesDeps {\n    11→  db: Db;\n    12→}\n    13→\n    14→/** Map DB game names to frontend game IDs */\n    15→const GAME_TO_FRONTEND: Record<string, string> = {\n    16→  coinflip: \"coinflip\",\n    17→  lord: \"lord-of-rngs\",\n    18→  closecall: \"close-call\",\n    19→};\n    20→\n    21→/** Map frontend/DB game names to canonical DB names */\n    22→const TO_DB_GAME: Record<string, string> = {\n    23→  coinflip: \"coinflip\",\n    24→  lord: \"lord\",\n    25→  closecall: \"closecall\",\n    26→  \"lord-of-rngs\": \"lord\",\n    27→  \"close-call\": \"closecall\",\n    28→};\n    29→\n    30→export function createProfileRoutes(deps: ProfileRoutesDeps) {\n    31→  const { db } = deps;\n    32→  const app = new Hono<AppEnv>();\n    33→\n    34→  app.get(\"/transactions\", async (c) => {\n    35→    const wallet = c.get(\"wallet\");\n    36→    if (!wallet) {\n    37→      return c.json({ error: \"Authentication required\" }, 401);\n    38→    }\n    39→\n    40→    // Parse query params\n    41→    const cursor = c.req.query(\"cursor\") || undefined;\n    42→    const limitParam = c.req.query(\"limit\");\n    43→    const gameParam = c.req.query(\"game\") || undefined;\n    44→\n    45→    // Validate & clamp limit\n    46→    let limit = 20;\n    47→    if (limitParam) {\n    48→      const parsed = parseInt(limitParam, 10);\n    49→      if (!isNaN(parsed) && parsed > 0) {\n    50→        limit = Math.min(parsed, 50);\n    51→      }\n    52→    }\n    53→\n    54→    // Map game filter to DB name (accept both DB and frontend names)\n    55→    let dbGame: string | undefined;\n    56→    if (gameParam) {\n    57→      dbGame = TO_DB_GAME[gameParam];\n    58→      if (!dbGame) {\n    59→        return c.json({ error: `Invalid game filter: ${gameParam}` }, 400);\n    60→      }\n    61→    }\n    62→\n    63→    try {\n    64→      const rows = await db.getTransactions(wallet, cursor, limit, dbGame);\n    65→\n    66→      const transactions = rows.map((row) => ({\n    67→        id: row.id,\n    68→        game: GAME_TO_FRONTEND[row.game] ?? row.game,\n    69→        matchId: row.match_id,\n    70→        txType: row.tx_type,\n    71→        amountLamports: String(row.amount_lamports),\n    72→        txSig: row.tx_sig,\n    73→        createdAt: row.created_at.toISOString(),\n    74→      }));\n    75→\n    76→      const nextCursor =\n    77→        transactions.length === limit\n    78→          ? String(transactions[transactions.length - 1]!.id)\n    79→          : null;\n    80→\n    81→      return c.json({ transactions, nextCursor });\n    82→    } catch (err) {\n    83→      logger.error(\"profile transactions query failed\", {\n    84→        wallet,\n    85→        error: err instanceof Error ? err.message : \"Unknown error\",\n    86→      });\n    87→      return c.json({ error: \"Failed to fetch transactions\" }, 500);\n    88→    }\n    89→  });\n    90→\n    91→  // POST /confirm-tx — frontend reports a confirmed on-chain transaction\n    92→  app.post(\"/confirm-tx\", async (c) => {\n    93→    const wallet = c.get(\"wallet\");\n    94→    if (!wallet) {\n    95→      return c.json({ error: \"Authentication required\" }, 401);\n    96→    }\n    97→\n    98→    const body = await c.req.json<{\n    99→      game?: string;\n   100→      matchId?: string;\n   101→      txType?: string;\n   102→      txSig?: string;\n   103→      amountLamports?: number;\n   104→    }>();\n   105→\n   106→    if (!body.game || !body.matchId || !body.txType || !body.txSig || !body.amountLamports) {\n   107→      return c.json({ error: \"Missing required fields: game, matchId, txType, txSig, amountLamports\" }, 400);\n   108→    }\n   109→\n   110→    const validTypes = [\"deposit\", \"refund\"];\n   111→    if (!validTypes.includes(body.txType)) {\n   112→      return c.json({ error: `Invalid txType: ${body.txType}. Must be one of: ${validTypes.join(\", \")}` }, 400);\n   113→    }\n   114→\n   115→    // Map to DB game name\n   116→    const dbGame = TO_DB_GAME[body.game];\n   117→    if (!dbGame) {\n   118→      return c.json({ error: `Invalid game: ${body.game}` }, 400);\n   119→    }\n   120→\n   121→    try {\n   122→      await db.insertTransaction({\n   123→        wallet,\n   124→        game: dbGame,\n   125→        matchId: body.matchId,\n   126→        txType: body.txType as \"deposit\" | \"refund\",\n   127→        amountLamports: body.amountLamports,\n   128→        txSig: body.txSig,\n   129→      });\n   130→      return c.json({ ok: true });\n   131→    } catch (err) {\n   132→      logger.error(\"confirm-tx failed\", {\n   133→        wallet,\n   134→        txType: body.txType,\n   135→        error: err instanceof Error ? err.message : \"Unknown error\",\n   136→      });\n   137→      return c.json({ error: \"Failed to record transaction\" }, 500);\n   138→    }\n   139→  });\n   140→\n   141→  return app;\n   142→}\n   143→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01VCdhEkVHxr9GNyPLZrZRLq","session_id":"91d95e74-c305-4801-b7f4-b036b613409b","uuid":"39de51f7-9fd8-40da-aa6d-5c804066a82d","timestamp":"2026-03-25T11:56:40.202Z"}
{"type":"system","subtype":"task_notification","task_id":"aab7dbb5c890344b7","tool_use_id":"toolu_01VCdhEkVHxr9GNyPLZrZRLq","status":"completed","output_file":"","summary":"Explore backend route patterns","usage":{"total_tokens":48991,"tool_uses":11,"duration_ms":37757},"uuid":"5823b2c5-3d79-49eb-a149-83b22bb9ccde","session_id":"91d95e74-c305-4801-b7f4-b036b613409b"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01VCdhEkVHxr9GNyPLZrZRLq","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I now have all the information you need. Here's a concrete breakdown:\n\n## GET Endpoint Structure — Key Examples\n\n### 1. **Basic Public GET (no auth required)**\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/routes/rounds.ts`\n\n```typescript\napp.get(\"/by-id/:matchId\", async (c) => {\n  const matchId = c.req.param(\"matchId\");\n  \n  // Validate input\n  if (!isHex16 && !isNumericTs) {\n    return c.json({ error: \"matchId must be a 16-char hex string or numeric timestamp\" }, 400);\n  }\n  \n  // Query DB\n  const round = await db.getRoundByMatchId(normalizedId);\n  if (round) {\n    return c.json(await formatRoundResponse(db, round));\n  }\n  \n  // Return 404 if not found\n  return c.json({ error: \"Round not found\" }, 404);\n});\n```\n\n### 2. **Authenticated GET (JWT required)**\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/routes/profile.ts`\n\nThe key is middleware setup in `index.ts` (lines 85–90):\n\n```typescript\n// Profile routes — authenticated GET endpoints (require JWT on all methods)\napp.use(\n  \"/profile/*\",\n  createJwtAuthMiddleware({ jwtSecret: config.jwtSecret, requireAllMethods: true }),\n);\napp.route(\"/profile\", createProfileRoutes({ db }));\n```\n\nThen in the route handler:\n\n```typescript\napp.get(\"/transactions\", async (c) => {\n  const wallet = c.get(\"wallet\");  // Extracted by JWT middleware\n  if (!wallet) {\n    return c.json({ error: \"Authentication required\" }, 401);\n  }\n  \n  // Query DB with authenticated wallet\n  const rows = await db.getTransactions(wallet, cursor, limit, dbGame);\n  return c.json({ transactions, nextCursor });\n});\n```\n\n### 3. **JWT Auth Middleware Details**\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/middleware/jwt-auth.ts`\n\n- Extracts `Authorization: Bearer <token>` header\n- Verifies HS256 JWT signature\n- Sets `c.set(\"wallet\", payload.sub)` in context (the token's `sub` claim is the wallet address)\n- Skips auth for GET requests by default **unless** `requireAllMethods: true` is set\n\n### 4. **AppEnv Type**\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/hono-env.ts`\n\n```typescript\nexport type AppEnv = {\n  Variables: {\n    wallet: string;  // Set by JWT middleware\n  };\n};\n```\n\nTyped routes use: `const app = new Hono<AppEnv>();` to get `c.get(\"wallet\")` with type safety.\n\n### 5. **Query Params & Validation Pattern**\n\nFrom `rounds.ts` and `profile.ts`:\n\n```typescript\nconst game = c.req.query(\"game\");\nconst limit = Math.min(Math.max(parseInt(c.req.query(\"limit\") ?? \"20\", 10) || 20, 1), 50);\nconst cursor = c.req.query(\"cursor\") || undefined;\n\n// Validate before querying DB\nif (!game || ![\"coinflip\", \"lord\"].includes(game)) {\n  return c.json({ error: \"game must be 'coinflip' or 'lord'\" }, 400);\n}\n```\n\n### 6. **Error Response Patterns**\n\n- **400**: Bad input (invalid game, missing required fields)\n- **401**: Authentication failed (missing JWT, invalid signature)\n- **404**: Resource not found (round doesn't exist)\n- **500**: Server error (DB query failed, log with context)\n- **503**: External service unavailable (e.g., Pyth price unavailable)\n\n---\n\n## Summary for Your Use Case\n\nIf you're building a GET endpoint that requires auth:\n\n1. **Wrap with middleware** in `index.ts`: \n   ```typescript\n   app.use(\"/your-path/*\", createJwtAuthMiddleware({ jwtSecret: config.jwtSecret, requireAllMethods: true }));\n   ```\n\n2. **Extract wallet in route**:\n   ```typescript\n   const app = new Hono<AppEnv>();\n   app.get(\"/your-endpoint\", async (c) => {\n     const wallet = c.get(\"wallet\");\n     // Query DB, return c.json({ ... }) or c.json({ error: \"...\" }, 404)\n   });\n   ```\n\n3. **Query params** via `c.req.query(\"key\")` and validate before DB access."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: aab7dbb5c890344b7 (use SendMessage with to: 'aab7dbb5c890344b7' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 49942\ntool_uses: 11\nduration_ms: 37823</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"91d95e74-c305-4801-b7f4-b036b613409b","uuid":"1d82a1a1-cca8-476e-a804-b2af179c1edc","timestamp":"2026-03-25T11:56:51.365Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Quickly find how other GET endpoints are structured in the backend routes. Look at:\n1. `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/routes/` — any existing route files showing GET endpoints\n2. How JWT auth middleware extracts wallet from context\n3. The AppEnv type and how Hono routes work in this codebase\n\nFocus on giving me a concrete example of a GET endpoint that returns data or 404.","agentId":"aab7dbb5c890344b7","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I now have all the information you need. Here's a concrete breakdown:\n\n## GET Endpoint Structure — Key Examples\n\n### 1. **Basic Public GET (no auth required)**\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/routes/rounds.ts`\n\n```typescript\napp.get(\"/by-id/:matchId\", async (c) => {\n  const matchId = c.req.param(\"matchId\");\n  \n  // Validate input\n  if (!isHex16 && !isNumericTs) {\n    return c.json({ error: \"matchId must be a 16-char hex string or numeric timestamp\" }, 400);\n  }\n  \n  // Query DB\n  const round = await db.getRoundByMatchId(normalizedId);\n  if (round) {\n    return c.json(await formatRoundResponse(db, round));\n  }\n  \n  // Return 404 if not found\n  return c.json({ error: \"Round not found\" }, 404);\n});\n```\n\n### 2. **Authenticated GET (JWT required)**\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/routes/profile.ts`\n\nThe key is middleware setup in `index.ts` (lines 85–90):\n\n```typescript\n// Profile routes — authenticated GET endpoints (require JWT on all methods)\napp.use(\n  \"/profile/*\",\n  createJwtAuthMiddleware({ jwtSecret: config.jwtSecret, requireAllMethods: true }),\n);\napp.route(\"/profile\", createProfileRoutes({ db }));\n```\n\nThen in the route handler:\n\n```typescript\napp.get(\"/transactions\", async (c) => {\n  const wallet = c.get(\"wallet\");  // Extracted by JWT middleware\n  if (!wallet) {\n    return c.json({ error: \"Authentication required\" }, 401);\n  }\n  \n  // Query DB with authenticated wallet\n  const rows = await db.getTransactions(wallet, cursor, limit, dbGame);\n  return c.json({ transactions, nextCursor });\n});\n```\n\n### 3. **JWT Auth Middleware Details**\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/middleware/jwt-auth.ts`\n\n- Extracts `Authorization: Bearer <token>` header\n- Verifies HS256 JWT signature\n- Sets `c.set(\"wallet\", payload.sub)` in context (the token's `sub` claim is the wallet address)\n- Skips auth for GET requests by default **unless** `requireAllMethods: true` is set\n\n### 4. **AppEnv Type**\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/hono-env.ts`\n\n```typescript\nexport type AppEnv = {\n  Variables: {\n    wallet: string;  // Set by JWT middleware\n  };\n};\n```\n\nTyped routes use: `const app = new Hono<AppEnv>();` to get `c.get(\"wallet\")` with type safety.\n\n### 5. **Query Params & Validation Pattern**\n\nFrom `rounds.ts` and `profile.ts`:\n\n```typescript\nconst game = c.req.query(\"game\");\nconst limit = Math.min(Math.max(parseInt(c.req.query(\"limit\") ?? \"20\", 10) || 20, 1), 50);\nconst cursor = c.req.query(\"cursor\") || undefined;\n\n// Validate before querying DB\nif (!game || ![\"coinflip\", \"lord\"].includes(game)) {\n  return c.json({ error: \"game must be 'coinflip' or 'lord'\" }, 400);\n}\n```\n\n### 6. **Error Response Patterns**\n\n- **400**: Bad input (invalid game, missing required fields)\n- **401**: Authentication failed (missing JWT, invalid signature)\n- **404**: Resource not found (round doesn't exist)\n- **500**: Server error (DB query failed, log with context)\n- **503**: External service unavailable (e.g., Pyth price unavailable)\n\n---\n\n## Summary for Your Use Case\n\nIf you're building a GET endpoint that requires auth:\n\n1. **Wrap with middleware** in `index.ts`: \n   ```typescript\n   app.use(\"/your-path/*\", createJwtAuthMiddleware({ jwtSecret: config.jwtSecret, requireAllMethods: true }));\n   ```\n\n2. **Extract wallet in route**:\n   ```typescript\n   const app = new Hono<AppEnv>();\n   app.get(\"/your-endpoint\", async (c) => {\n     const wallet = c.get(\"wallet\");\n     // Query DB, return c.json({ ... }) or c.json({ error: \"...\" }, 404)\n   });\n   ```\n\n3. **Query params** via `c.req.query(\"key\")` and validate before DB access."}],"totalDurationMs":37823,"totalTokens":49942,"totalToolUseCount":11,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1915,"cache_read_input_tokens":46829,"output_tokens":1195,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1915},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
